column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Sunny day- very little wind- warm spring day.
Calm winds- cloudless- finally warm- about 70 which ended record low temps for this area and much of the Midwest. Lake flat with only one boat with water skier.
Mostly cloudy- zero wind- lake glassy. Surface temperature 76 F.
Lake calm with no wind- overcast skies with almost total cloud cover. Warm Spring day.
Wind south at 1-5 mph- lake calm with ripples. Porter the dog and Beverly the spouse assisting. Partly sunny. Warm- lower 70s.
Total cloud cover. Wind 0-5 mph from the NNW. Slight ripple on the water. Air temperature about 70 F. Porter the dog assisting.
Sunny day- few cumulus clouds present- wind from the north at 0-5 mph. Warm for this altogether cool summer. Faithful wife assisting- and of course Porter the dog.

Partly cloudy with high chirrus clouds- wind 5 mph from the SSW. Slight ripple on lake. Air temperature about 60 degrees. Temperature sensor unexpectedly had a dead battery- so my readings of dissolved oxygen are without water temperatures. However- the surface temperature from the fish locater indicated 58 degrees.
Partly cloudy with high chirrus clouds. Winds 0-5 mph from South- slight ripple on lake. Saw Great Blue Heron . Warm- about upper 60s.
Mostly sunny with some puffy cumulus clouds present- wind south at about 5 mph. Warm day with temps in mid 70s. No boating activity on lake.
Wind West at 5-10 mph- 6 inch waves on lake. Partly cloudy with puffy cumulus clouds evident.
Mostly sunny- calm wind from the WNW at 0-5 mph. Slight ripple on water's surface. Beautiful day in the upper 50's.

Clear skies- sunny- unseasonably warm- 80 degrees F. Wind 0-5 mph from the SW- waves 2-4 inch ripples. Beautiful day for Spring ( not to mention Summer ). Assistants are Porter the dog- and Beverly the wife. Clear- sunny day- warm- 80 degrees F. Unseasonably hot. Wind 0-5 mph from the SW causing 2-4 inch ripples on the lake. Beautiful day for Spring. This may be the only day of Summer   Assistants are Porter the dog- and Beverly the wife.
Partly sunny with cumulus clouds- wind WNW variable at 0-5 mph. Beautiful day- temperature at low 70's. Slight ripple on the surface. Porter the dog assisting.
Sunny with wind 5-10 mph out of the S-SW. Small waves on lake. Warm- in the 80's- blue sky with cumulus clouds.

Mostly cloudy with wind 0-5 mph from the west. Slight ripples on lake with no boat traffic. Many geese on lake with a large number on one riparian owner's lawn frontage filled with the beasts. Yet another reason to keep your frontage natural- to avoid the geese. Temperature about 70- nice day. Porter the Dog assisting.

Mostly sunny with puffy cumulus clouds present in blue sky. Slight ripple on lake from wind which is NW at 0-3 mph. Air temperature about 70 degrees Fahrenheit. First nice day after a lot of rain. Porter the dog assisting. Great blue Heron observed.   First sunny day after many days of rain- puffy cumulus clouds present in blue sky. Air temperature about 70 degrees Fahrenheit. Great blue Heron seen. Wind 0-3 mph from the NW- slight ripple on water. Porter the dog assisting.
Cloudless blue sky- wind variable at 0-2 mph from the S. Saw two great blue herons. No other boats on lake. Porter the dog assisting.

Blue sky- very few scattered cumulus clouds. Air temperature about 65 degrees F. Wind from the North at 3-5 mph. Slight ripples on water surface. Surface water temperature 66 degrees F. I am alone on the lake. Beautiful day
Hot day- about 80 F- light S wind at about 4 mph. Blue sky with scattered cumulus clouds- mostly sunny. No boats on lake.
Calm winds- mostly sunny with scattered cumulus clouds. Slight ripple on water surface. No boat traffic present. Air temperature 76-80 degrees F.
Total cloud cover- gray day- wind SSW at 0-3 mph. Surface water temperature 70 degrees F. Air temperature at low 60 s.
Hazy day- warm- temperature 76 F. Wind NNW at 5 mph. I am the only boat on the lake- very peaceful. Porter the dog assisting.
Partly cloudy- air temperature 73- wind SW at 5-10 mph- slight chop on water- algae suspended in water.

Finally- a warm sunny day after many cool and rainy ones. Air temperature 74- winds South at 5-10 mph. Light chop on lake. Partly sunny with cumulus clouds. Rained last night and this morning- Porter the Dog assisting.
Beautiful day- mostly clear skies with cumulus clouds- wind light at 0-5 mph from the N.E. Surface water temperature
